<l>vakarak kiḷavi nāṉmoḻi yīṟṟatu</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>The sound <foreign xml:lang="ta">v</foreign> stands at the end of four words.<note place="foot">Accord. to <foreign xml:lang="ta">Iḷam.,</foreign> these four are <foreign xml:lang="ta">av</foreign> ' that ', <foreign xml:lang="ta">iv</foreign> ' this ' <foreign xml:lang="ta">uv</foreign> ' the intermediate ' and <foreign xml:lang="ta">tev,</foreign>
            ' enmity '. I am rather inclined to think that the fourth one <foreign xml:lang="ta">
            Tolk.</foreign> had in mind was <foreign xml:lang="ta">ev</foreign> ' which '. </note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
